column21: "The related Littorina angulifera (Lamarck) (Mangrove Periwinkle) showed regular consumption of lichens or fungal propagules in mangroves, with fungal tissue showing in fecal pellets 80% of the time (Kohlmeyer and Bebout 1986). In cases such as that of W. mucosa in the littoral zone, phenolic concentrations are linked to decreased herbivory (Higgins et al. 2015). Despite this, some indirect evidence showing increased grazing of H. maura transplanted to the lower littoral zone suggests some preference by littorinids, but further evidence is needed for confirmation (Higgins et al. 2015)."
